course, assuming both players play equally well (you can beat anyone who do mistakes or react slowly).<br>
<br>
Even using the assortments of skald powers, you are in trouble. Frontloading style+DD+DD+mez ? he can frontload style+insta lightning+pbae DD for almost as much damage (and he has cast the big lightning and eventually the mjolnir if the fight started at range). While you wait during mez's duration for your timers to recycle, so do his timers.<br>
Kiting ? He has more power at range than you. Your snare and speed won't help. If you are at range to DD him, he has plenty of range to cast his varied flavors of lightning spells.<br>
Meleeing ? He his better at straight melee : better damage add, better spec (2.0), shield. Shield stun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/14/03 5:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=451.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> So</span><hr size=1> So ... how to win ?<br>
<br>
Well, you might be a better player (the guy behind the keyboard) than him, or have an edge RA or equipment wise.<br>
<br>
Else, as other poster suggested, the only way to even the playing field is to make a creative use of charged/proccing items, alchemy ... if your opponent didn't think about using such items. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmytheskald>Grimmytheskald</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/15/03 7:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=451.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: So</span><hr size=1> Same way you might beat a healer in a one-rounder.<br>
<br>
Get him to low hit points where he is flirting with hitting the IP button.  Mez him at that point, move behind for your high damage rear-positional and hit that and both DD's at the same time.  You have to kill him before he IP's or it's all over but the soft weeping and lamenting. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.regal-image.com/customgraphics/grimnorbloodsong.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mance>Mance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/16/03 4:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=451.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: So</span><hr size=1> Well...<br>
